The paper deals with generating adversarial examples for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks and optimization techniques also suggests that it could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the generated adversarial examples, which could be relevant to the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques to generate adversarial examples could also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
